",\"content\":\"Yes, I am a licensed and Board certified engineer. My Board certification comes from the National Academy of Forensic Engineers. Additionally, I am an NCEES Record Holder,  meaning I can typically get licensed in any state within 30 days.\",\"code_block\":\"\"},{\"col_class\":\"col-12\",\"col_style\":\"\",\"col_id\":\"\",\"title\":\"What is your availability?\",\"content\":\"I am accepting new cases and am flexible and available on my clients schedules. I take pride in meeting all my clients deadlines.\",\"code_block\":\"\"},{\"col_class\":\"col-12\",\"col_style\":\"\",\"col_id\":\"\",\"title\":\"What is your billing rate?\",\"content\":\"My rates are very reasonable. I have two set rates for testimony time, such as in deposition or trial. The second, a lower rate, is for all other time (research, report writing, etc.) I collect an initial retainer and invoice against that.\",\"code_block\":\"\"},{\"col_class\":\"col-12\",\"col_style\":\"\",\"col_id\":\"\",\"title\":\"What is your educational background?\",\"content\":\"Ive been blessed with the opportunity to gain excellent academic credentials.\\u003cbr\\u003e\\u003cbr\\u003eI have a Bachelor of Science in Electrical Engineering (BSEE) from Lehigh University in Bethlehem, PA. My first Masters degree is in Telecommunications Engineering, and my second Masters degree is in Engineering Management- both from the University of Colorado at Boulder. I also completed about 2/3 of an MSEE degree in RF engineering from Drexel University in Philadelphia before moving to Colorado.\\u003cbr\\u003e\\u003cbr\\u003eLastly, I procured the highest credential available in the quality sciences: the Six Sigma Master Black Belt. This required eight graduate courses (24 credit hours) in applied statistics and research at the University of Colorado.\\u003cbr\\u003e\",\"code_block\":\"\"},{\"col_class\":\"col-12\",\"col_style\":\"\",\"col_id\":\"\",\"title\":\"How many years of experience do you have?\",\"content\":\"I hav